text: Corophium multisetosum is a small (up to 9mm) European amphipod crustacean of the family Corophiidae. It builds mud burrows in clay or sand in fresh or weakly brackish habitats. Corophium multisetosum occurs on coasts of the Netherlands, France, Germany, Poland and the British Isles. ==External links== * M.J. de Kluijver & S.S.
